BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260212T180000Z
DTEND:20260212T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260212T000000Z
SUMMARY:Scholarly Write-In
DESCRIPTION:Write and work in solidarity with other IU scholars. We offer a 
 silent work environment with coffee and natural light. The write-in is open 
 to all graduate students (at any stage of their degree program).\n\nMeets 
 weekly throughout the semester\, Thursday from 1-3pm. No meeting during 
 spring break.\n\nCo-sponsored by Writing Tutorial Services and the IU 
 Libraries.\n\nDrop in or come weekly as your schedule permits.
LOCATION:IQ Wall- E157H
ORGANIZER;CN="Alyssa Denneler":MAILTO:alydenn@iu.edu
CATEGORIES:Citing, Writing & Research Tools
UID:LibCal-1228-16225021
URL:https://iub.libcal.com/event/16225021
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260218T170000Z
DTEND:20260218T183000Z
DTSTAMP:20260218T000000Z
SUMMARY:Center for Survey Research Consultations
DESCRIPTION:Make an appointment now! 
 https://iub.libcal.com/appointments/csr\n\nYou have the option to schedule 
 on Zoom or in-person.\n\nThe Center for Survey Research consults with 
 faculty\, staff\, and students across a wide range of substantive 
 disciplines spanning business\, education\, the social sciences\, and the 
 health sciences. We are happy to assist with any qualitative or 
 quantitative research project by providing consultation on:\n research 
 design\n questionnaire development and review\n sample design\n online 
 interface and reporting portal development\n database and data collection 
 instrument programming including Qualtrics online survey software\n 
 usability testing\n sample management including high-volume email 
 campaigns\n data collection using online\, telephone\, mail\, and 
 face-to-face administration\n qualitative methods (semi-structured 
 interviews\, focus groups\, observations\, etc.)\n data processing\n data 
 analysis\n\nTakes place in the Wells Library Scholars' Commons\, first 
 floor of the east tower. No question too big or too small!
ORGANIZER;CN="CSR Center for Survey Research":MAILTO:afbowers@iu.edu
CATEGORIES:Scholars' Commons Consulting
UID:LibCal-1228-16110422
URL:https://iub.libcal.com/calendar/workshops/csr
END:VEVENT
